# Subscribe

---

If you want to keep up with any changes on this site, but don't feel like checking it often, you can subscribe to any of the feeds listed below.
Raw feeds aren't for human consumption -- you'll need to copy these links into an RSS / Atom reader.

- [*`Atom feed`*](/atom.xml): The preferred method using the superior Atom format
- [*`RSS feed`*](/rss.xml): For readers that don't support Atom

:::

## RSS / Atom Readers

---

[RSS](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RSS) [^rss] (Really Simple Syndication) and [Atom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atom_(web_standard)) [^atom] (Atom Syndication Format) feeds offer another way to get content from this website. 
Subscribing to RSS / Atom feeds allows you to keep track of multiple websites in a single feed reader program (desktop, app, browser extension),
which monitors sites for new content, removing the need for the user to manually do so.

::: tabset

# Windows

Other than my servers, I run windows on all my computers, so these are the programs I'd use.

- [RSSOwl](https://github.com/Xyrio/RSSOwlnix/): This is what I personally use, but it's a bit outdated. 
- [Raven Reader](https://ravenreader.app/): Great UI, open source, and available on linux too. I'd upgrade to this if I ever got a new computer.
- [Fluent Reader](https://hyliu.me/fluent-reader/): A more modern RSS reader. Can be run locally or self-hosted.

